pamsignal (0.2.3-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Security: enforce a _EXE allowlist on every journal entry so
    unprivileged users can no longer inject fake PAM events via
    logger(1) to trigger false alerts or brute-force lockouts. Only
    entries whose _EXE resolves to sshd / sudo / su / login /
    systemd-logind under a system prefix are processed; entries with a
    missing _EXE are dropped.
  * Fix brute-force tracker: zero last_brute_alert_usec on the
    evict-and-reuse path so a new IP doesn't inherit the evicted IP's
    alert cooldown.
  * Fix SIGHUP reload: preserve the in-memory brute-force tracking
    table across reloads instead of zeroing it. Existing per-IP attempt
    counts and cooldowns survive a config reload.

